String class:
    String is the most widely used class in java. It has a lot of methods
    which can help us process String data. For example
        1)equals => is used to compare two Strings
        2)toLowerCase => converts Strings to lowercase
        3)EqualsIgnoreCase => compares two Strings ignoring case
        4)toUpperCase => convert Strings to uppercase
        5)Contains => checks if a word or character is present in a String
        6)StartsWith => checks if a String starts with specific word or char
        7)EndsWith  => checks if a String ends with specific word or char
        8)indexOf => returns the index of a char
        9)charAt => returns the char at specified index
        10)trims => used to remove spaces before and after the String